   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PPC Barnet DRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Support to industrial, social and infrastructure development: the project will expand local production of cement, reduce dependency on imports and save foreign exchange. Ultimately, the project will help reduce cement prices and support the development of the housing and infrastructure sectors. 2. Local supply chain development: the project will create new SME business opportunities due to increased demand for the supply of raw materials, transportation and distribution services. 3. Job creation: The project will create about 270 jobs for locals and many more indirect jobs in the value chain. 4. South-south investment: IFC will be supporting a South African corporate investing up north in Sub-Saharan Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project involves the construction of a greenfield integrated cement plant of 1.25 million tons per annum (Mtpa) capacity to supply cement locally.</narrative>
  </description>
